<section class="py-24 px-6 relative overflow-hidden">
  <!-- Subtle background glow -->
  <div class="absolute top-1/2 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-[600px] h-[400px] bg-brand-accent/3 rounded-full blur-[100px] pointer-events-none"></div>

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center relative z-10">
    <h2 class="font-mono text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-8">
      Robots are collaborators.<br />
      <span class="text-brand-accent">Treat them like it.</span>
    </h2>
    <p class="text-brand-muted text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
      When you work with an OpenClaw, you're working with a teammate on a different machine.
      It has its own identity, its own memory, its own way of doing things. You need a way to
      shape that, and a way to share work back and forth.
    </p>
    <p class="text-brand-muted text-lg leading-relaxed">
      ContextMate is the secure bridge. Sync your robot's configuration from your laptop.
      Get documents it creates back on your machine. Keep multiple robots in sync.
      All encrypted, all automatic, all without giving the robot access to anything else.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
